{"comments":"Rotational Symmetry — N-fold rotation invariance.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nAn N-fold rotational symmetry means the shape looks identical after\nrotation by 360°/N. For example:\n- 2-fold: looks same after 180° rotation (rectangle)\n- 3-fold: looks same after 120° rotation (equilateral triangle)\n- 4-fold: looks same after 90° rotation (square)\n- ∞-fold: looks same after any rotation (circle)\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- Radial UI elements (color wheels, dials)\n- Regular polygon generation\n- Mandala and snowflake patterns\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n- Geometry.Angle (Degrees)\n- Data.Maybe (Maybe)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["folds",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[81,65],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Rotational.purs","start":[81,28]},"title":"RotationalSymmetry"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","Rotational"],"RotationalSymmetry"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,62],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Rotational.purs","start":[83,1]},"title":"eqRotationalSymmetry"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","Rotational"],"RotationalSymmetry"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,6